climbs.name: Trundle Cracks
climbs.fa: Alan Bartlett and Chris Miller, October 1994

content.description:
Climb double cracks down low through a slabby section of rock midway and then move left to finish in a crack just right of

My Little Pretty

.
content.location:
Starts 20 feet right of

Channel Surfer

.

content.description: Tough start (bouldery) leads to dicey face moves which leads into a bowl. After this a medium cam is needed. Next, right out on the upper face.
content.protection: 4 bolts and runners with a med. cam
content.location: North face high on the dome.

content.description: Climb a fun, steep, pocketed face.
content.location: This climb starts near the left end of the ledge at mid-height, approximately where Channel Surfer ends.

content.description: Climbs up to and along the right side of a curving crack that starts high on the face. Great rock quality on this route.
content.protection:
Top-rope from anchors on

Trembling Toto's

.
content.location: Right of center on the upper face that starts off the ledge.

content.description: Moving from the West face around the arete to the North face seems to be the crux.
content.protection: Four or five quick draws and some runners for the anchors
content.location: This route is high on the dome and far left on the west face where a meter wide ledge extends along the faces base.  Up and around the arete to the north side where the route merges with Trembling Toto's.

content.description: The start is the crux.  Clip the bolt and move into easy crack climbing.
content.protection: One bolt, and then a varied assortment of cams
content.location: Far left on the North face.

climbs.name: Channel Surfer
climbs.fa: Chris Miller and Alan Bartlett, October 1994

content.description: Start with the right crack, and then move to the left crack.  Do a fairly committing crux thin lieback up to easier ground.
content.location: This route climbs the lower part of the wall, to the ledge at mid-height.  It is near the left end, and uses a pair of thin cracks.
